<ul class="task-constraints">
<li><b>Time limit:</b> 1.00 s</li>
<li><b>Memory limit:</b> 512 MB</li>
</ul>
<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1724">
Consider a directed weighted graph having $n$ nodes and $m$ edges. Your task is to calculate the minimum path length from node $1$ to node $n$ with exactly $k$ edges.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line contains three integers $n$, $m$ and $k$: the number of nodes and edges, and the length of the path. The nodes are numbered $1,2,\dots,n$.<br />
<br />
Then, there are m lines describing the edges. Each line contains three integers $a$, $b$ and $c$: there is an edge from node $a$ to node $b$ with weight $c$.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print the minimum path length. If there are no such paths, print $-1$.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 100$<br />
<li>$1 \le m \le n(n-1)$<br />
<li>$1 \le k \le 10^9$<br />
<li>$1 \le a,b \le n$<br />
<li>$1 \le c \le 10^9$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>3 4 8<br />
1 2 5<br />
2 3 4<br />
3 1 1<br />
3 2 2</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>27</code>    </div>
